<br>
Here is what Moorgard - the &quot;Community Relations Manager for EverQuest II&quot; and is the person in charge of disseminating game details to the public.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Moorgard wrote:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
Certainly the gods have an interest in the mortals of Norrath, for many of the reasons postulated in this thread. The gods are often petty beings, and even the &quot;best&quot; of them can be prideful and vain. <br>
<br>
One might wonder how the gods would react to mortals ravaging their planes and killing the embodiments of their powers. Perhaps the gods would have different ideas about what course of action to take. Maybe, as they've done in the past, some of them would set their plans in motion... <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
and one other post he made:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Moorgard wrote:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
You're assuming that you'll be choosing a deity.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
It looks pretty obvious from both of these statements that the gods will be there - but there will be no choice in who your deity is going to be.  <br>
<br>
Maybe they will tie in some event in your characters life that includes a visit from a deity that is based on the actions your character has taken and choices you have made?  EQ II is definately going to be a completely different beast than EQ is.  <br>
<br>
